HEADWORD: Unprince
<hw>Un*prince"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>prince</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of the
character or authority of a prince; to divest of principality of
sovereignty.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

